U.S. Open Winner Novak Djokovic Withdraws From Davis Cup With Back Injury

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-09-17T16:48:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/u-s-open-winner-novak-djokovic-withdraws-from-davis-cup-with-back-injury.html
Defending champion Serbia and
 France  won their doubles matches today to avoid elimination from
the Davis Cup tennis semifinals.  Viktor Troicki and Nenad Zimonjic defeated Juan Ignacio
Chela and Juan Monaco 7-6 (7-4), 6-4, 6-2 as Serbia pulled to
within 2-1 in its series with Argentina in Belgrade. Serbia is
playing without U.S. Open champion Novak Djokovic, who withdrew
from the competition yesterday with an injury.  Michael Llodra and Jo-Wilfried Tsonga beat Fernando
Verdasco and Feliciano Lopez 6-1, 6-2, 6-0 to cut Spain’s lead
to 2-1 in Cordoba. Rafael Nadal and  David Ferrer  won their
singles matches yesterday for the host.  The best-of-five series will be decided in tomorrow’s
reverse singles matches. The winners advance to the Davis Cup
final Dec. 2-4.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  